The paper discusses the basic communications network infrastructure of Iran, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses censorship and the use of private addresses, which could fall under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The mention of a 'dual stack' approach could also fall under the category of computer systems organization (cs.CY) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses DNS entries, which could fall under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
